    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "\t RECORD STORE AR \u2013 USER GUIDE\nMAP NAME\nAt the top of every instruction
    page, you will see the Map Name.\n\nEach map must have a unique name.\n\nMap
    names must not contain spaces.\n(Tip: Use underscores _ or dashes - if needed.)\n\nExample:\n
    MyRecordStore_Map01\n\n KEY CONCEPTS\nAnchor: A fixed point in the Augmented
    Reality (AR) space where you can attach virtual objects like walls, instruments,
    or picture frames.\n\nCloud Anchor: An anchor stored on the cloud platform, allowing
    you or others to resolve it later and display virtual objects in the exact same
    position as before.\n\nANCHOR PAGE\nPurpose: Create anchors at positions where
    you want to place virtual objects in the environment.\n\nImportant Notes When
    Placing Anchors:\n\nOnly place anchors when the AR environment quality is labeled
    as: Sufficient, Good, or Excellent.\n\nThe app will display the current environment
    quality \u2013 if it's low (e.g., Insufficient), move the device slowly and scan
    more of the environment to improve tracking.\n\nCLOUD ANCHOR PAGE\nPurpose: Manage
    and process operations related to Cloud Anchors.\n\n Main Features:\n\nUpload
    anchors to the cloud.\n\nView a list of previously created Cloud Anchor IDs.\n\nResolve
    Cloud Anchors to reload previously set up environments.\n\n WALL PAGE\nPurpose:
    Customize walls and object clusters attached to them.\n\nFunctions:\n\nAdjust
    wall size using drag and touch gestures.\n\nMove the wall to a new position (still
    attached to the anchor).\n\nEdit object clusters such as:\n\n Instrument Showcase\n\nPicture
    Frame\n\n OBJECT PAGE\nPurpose: Customize and manage individual objects in the
    AR space.\n\nFeatures:\n\nAdjust the scale of virtual objects (make them larger
    or smaller as needed).\n\nView the scanned environment map for better spatial
    understanding.\n\nUpload the map to the cloud for future use and synchronization."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: ef671587b5962194b988c24c1c624b2f, type: 2}
